# UK Recipes

Welcome to the UK section. Here you’ll find classic British dishes and a growing collection of traditional recipes.

- Fish and Chips – Crispy battered fish served with chunky chips and tartar sauce
- Full English Breakfast – A hearty plate with eggs, bacon, sausages, beans, tomatoes, mushrooms, and toast
- Bangers and Mash – Sausages served over creamy mashed potatoes with onion gravy
- Beef Wellington – Beef fillet wrapped in pâté and puff pastry, baked until golden
- Cornish Pasty – A baked pastry filled with beef, potatoes, swede, and onion
- Sticky Toffee Pudding – A rich date sponge cake soaked in toffee sauce
- Shepherd’s Pie – Minced lamb and vegetables topped with mashed potato and baked
- Victoria Sponge Cake – Light sponge layers filled with jam and whipped cream
- Toad in the Hole – Sausages baked in a Yorkshire pudding batter
- Chicken Tikka Masala – Marinated chicken in a creamy, spiced tomato sauce
- Ploughman’s Lunch – A cold platter of cheese, bread, pickles, and salad
- Scotch Eggs – Boiled eggs wrapped in sausage meat, breaded, and fried or baked
- Eton Mess – Crushed meringue mixed with whipped cream and fresh strawberries
- Trifle – Layers of sponge cake, custard, fruit, jelly, and cream
- Lancashire Hotpot – Slow-cooked lamb and onions topped with sliced potatoes
